    {
      "id": "04429ee7900301afeb2ce5c547e01943723cbacb",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 104,
        "name": "Niu Yawei",
        "email": "yawei.niu@intel.com",
        "username": "niu",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-10-10 11:24:01.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 12:\n\nHi, LiXi\n\nCould you share the design document? I think following concerns needs be decribed in the design doc:\n\n- How to enable/disable user/group quota for specific pool?\n- How is qsd_instace/qmt_pool allocated and prepared?\n- When default pool (mdt/ost) quota and specific pool quota are both enabled, how is the quota enforced?\n- Interoperability with old client. (I see protocol changes in the code)\n- Upgrade problem: how to deal with old system which doesn't have pool id in EA? I'm not sure adding pool id in EA is a good idea, which looks redundant, since there is already pool name in EA.\n- When there are many pools enforced quota, pool count * 2 threads will be started for quota recovery, I'm wondering if we need to change the reintegration logic bit to reduce thread count?\n- Test cases.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 12
    },
    {
      "id": "9601a57d39d01f727231266b7270baee52f05cf2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 337,
        "name": "Li Xi",
        "email": "lixi@ddn.com",
        "username": "LiX"
      },
      "date": "2013-10-10 11:39:00.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 12:\n\nHi Yawei,\n\nSure, a design document which decribes those things will be written soon. But I am currently so busy at working on a bug of the patch. I will write one as soon as possible.\n\nThanks!",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 12
    },
